There is currently NO `[features]` section in this `Cargo.toml`.

### Task

Add a `[features]` section to `crates/roko-cli/Cargo.toml` with a single feature
flag: `legacy-orchestrate`.

#### 1. Add `[features]` section

Place the `[features]` section after the `[lints]` section and before the `[[bin]]`
section. This follows the conventional Cargo.toml ordering:
`[package]` → `[lints]` → `[features]` → `[[bin]]` → `[dependencies]` → `[dev-dependencies]`

```toml
[features]
## Enable the legacy orchestrate.rs plan runner (the pre-WorkflowEngine path).
## NOT included in default features — opt-in only.
legacy-orchestrate = []
```

The feature has no dependency implications (empty array). It is a pure cfg flag
used by `#[cfg(feature = "legacy-orchestrate")]` guards in Rust source files
(added in R02).

#### 2. Verify no default features

Do NOT add a `default` key. The absence of `default = [...]` means no features
are enabled by default, which is the desired behavior — the v2 WorkflowEngine
path is the default, and `legacy-orchestrate` must be explicitly opted into.

